remonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":96,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":107,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Thomas Clapp was born about 1462, in Devon, England. She had at least 1 son with Thomas Clapp."},"et":{"about 1462–":"umbes 1462–Surnud","1460–1538":"1460–1538","1500–1555":"1500–1555","1462–Female":"1462–Surnud","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1555":"1555","1462":"1462","1460":"1460","about 1462":"umbes 1462","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","Sidbury, Devon, England":"Sidbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"about 1462–":"noin 1462–Kuollut","1460–1538":"1460–1538","1500–1555":"1500–1555","1462–Female":"1462–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1555":"1555","1462":"1462","1460":"1460","about 1462":"noin 1462","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","Sidbury, Devon, England":"Sidbury, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"about 1462–":"environ 1462–Décédée","1460–1538":"1460–1538","1500–1555":"1500–1555","1462–Female":"1462–Décédée","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1500":"1500","1555":"1555","1462":"1462","1460":"1460","about 1462":"environ 1462","1549":"154